//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_depot_levy}

NOTE: This operation creates an
{rbtgi_depot}
- a cohesive unit of Recipe Bottle infrastructure including the depot project, build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool
that share their productive lifecycle.

The
{rbtr_payor}
creates a new depot infrastructure from the
{rbtgi_payor_project}.
The operation accepts no CLI parameters; depot identity is read from the kindled regime as `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)`.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_payor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_payor_authenticate}

//axhos_step
. *Validate region against Artifact Registry locations*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations/list[locations.list] for the authenticated project
.. {rbbc_require}
`{rbrr_gcp_region}` present in the returned location set

//axhos_step
. *Derive Depot Identity*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«WORKER_POOL_STEM»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-pool` (resolved by `RBDC_GCB_POOL_STEM`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_BUCKET»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}b-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_GCS_BUCKET`)
.. NOTE: Joint length `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}` + `d-` + `${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` ≤ 30 chars (GCP project ID limit) is enforced upstream by `zrbrr_enforce` at regime kindle time, so this step performs no length validation.

//axhos_step
. *Create Depot Project*:
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/create[projects.create] with:
... projectId: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... displayName: `«RBGC_DEPOT_DISPLAY_PREFIX» «RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... NOTE: This displayName prefix anchors CRM v3 search-based depot discrimination used by {rbtgo_depot_list}.
... parent: `{rbrp_parent_type}s/{rbrp_parent_id}` (if parent_type != `none`)
.. {rbbc_await}
returned operation
.. {rbbc_require}
project creation successful
.. NOTE: Project name collision against the GCP soft-delete graveyard surfaces here as fatal — re-using a moniker after `{rbtgo_depot_unmake}` requires waiting out the 30-day retention window. The operator-visible "fails if exists" property is intentional under the (CLOUD_PREFIX, MONIKER) shape.

//axhos_step
. *Link Billing Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/billing/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects/updateBillingInfo[cloudbilling.projects.updateBillingInfo] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. Set billingAccountName: `billingAccounts/{rbrp_billing_account_id}`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response confirming billing linkage

//axhos_step
. *Get Depot Project Number*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PROJECT_NUMBER»` from `.name` field (CRM v3 returns `projects/{number}`)
.. {rbbc_require}
valid numeric project number after extracting from name

//axhos_step
. *Enable Depot Project APIs*:
.. For each service in [`artifactregistry`, `cloudbuild`, `containeranalysis`, `iam`, `serviceusage`, `storage`]:
... Execute
{rbtoe_api_enable}
with service name and `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_require}
all APIs enabled successfully

//axhos_step
. *Create Private Worker Pool*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.workerPools/create[workerPools.create] with:
... parent: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... workerPoolId: `«WORKER_POOL_STEM»`
... body:
+
----
{
  "privatePoolV1Config": {
    "workerConfig": {
      "machineType": "«RBRR_GCB_MACHINE_TYPE»"
    }
  }
}
----
.. NOTE:
{rbrr_gcb_machine_type}
is a Compute Engine machine type (e.g., `e2-standard-2`), consumed at pool creation time.
Pool scales to zero workers when idle — no idle cost accrues.
.. Treat HTTP 409 CONFLICT as success (pool already exists — idempotent)

//axhos_step
. *Verify IAM Propagation*:
.. NOTE: After API enablement, IAM permissions may not be immediately available due to eventual consistency.
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/list[artifactregistry.repositories.list] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` in `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
.. Poll at `RBGC_EVENTUAL_CONSISTENCY_SEC` intervals until HTTP 200 or `RBGC_MAX_CONSISTENCY_SEC` timeout
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response confirming IAM propagation complete
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if timeout: "IAM propagation timeout - artifactregistry API not accessible"

//axhos_step
. *Create Build Bucket*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/json_api/v1/buckets/insert[storage.buckets.insert] with:
... name: `«BUILD_BUCKET»`
... location: `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... project: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... lifecycle rule: delete objects after 1 day

//axhos_step
. *Create Container Repository*:
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/create[artifactregistry.repositories.create] with:
... repositoryId: `«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
... format: `DOCKER`
... location: `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... parent: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}`
.. {rbbc_await}
returned operation

//axhos_step
. *Create
{rbtr_mason}
Service Account*:
.. NOTE: The
{rbtr_mason}
replaces Cloud Build's implicit service account to provide deterministic permissions and predictable authorization within the depot infrastructure.
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
... accountId: `mason-«RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... displayName: `«RBGC_DEPOT_DISPLAY_PREFIX» mason «RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... project: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«MASON_EMAIL»` from response `.email` field

//axhos_step
. *Configure
{rbtr_mason}
Permissions*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_repo} on `«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.writer`
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_bucket} on `«BUILD_BUCKET»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/storage.objectViewer`
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} on `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/viewer`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/logging.logWriter`

//axhos_step
. *Enable Cloud Build service agent to impersonate
{rbtr_mason}*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_sa} on `«MASON_EMAIL»`
.. Add member: `serviceAccount:service-«PROJECT_NUMBER»@gcp-sa-cloudbuild.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
.. Grant role: `roles/iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator`
.. NOTE: Cloud Build service agent is Google-provisioned (auto-created when Cloud Build API is enabled), not a user-created service account. The `tokenCreator` role enables build steps running as {rbtr_mason} (via the build JSON's `serviceAccount` field) to generate fresh access tokens for GCP API calls — required for GAR authentication (docker login, crane push). This is distinct from `serviceAccountUser` (actAs), which the {rbtr_director} holds on {rbtr_mason} for submitting builds.
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM binding successful

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Confirm Depot Creation*:
.. {rbbc_show}
single-line success banner naming `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` and the
{rbtgo_governor_mantle}
follow-up hint

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Update Depot Tracking*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_depot_list_update}
to refresh per-moniker depot fact files

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates depot infrastructure with configured build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool — all derived from `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)`.
Proceed to
{rbtgo_governor_mantle}
to create the
{rbtr_governor}
for this depot.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_delete}

NOTE: This operation jettisons a single image tag from
{rbtgi_repository}
using the Docker Registry HTTP API V2 implemented by
{gar_service}.

`rbfl_jettison` is locator-generic: the same procedure backs
{rbtga_ark}
hallmark members,
reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.
The package path embedded in the
{rbst_locator}
selects the domain — the procedure itself does not branch.

NOTE: To delete an entire {rbtga_ark} (the full `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/` subtree — every basename including `image`, `about`, `vouch`, and any `pouch`/`diags`/`attest` tags present), use {rbtgo_ark_abjure} instead.

NOTE: Jettisoning an interior member of a reliquary subtree (e.g., a single tool image) leaves a hole in an otherwise-coherent set. The operator accepts this piecemeal-by-image semantic; recovery is nuclear: re-run {rbtgo_depot_inscribe} to restore the full reliquary corpus. The operation provides no integrity guard against such interior holes.

The
{rbtr_director}
jettisons an image by {rbst_locator}:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_locator}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_LOCATOR»` provided as first argument in `package-path:tag` format
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Locator parameter required (package-path:tag)"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed (no colon): "Invalid locator format. Expected package-path:tag"
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PACKAGE_PATH»` as portion before the final colon (e.g., `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/image`, `{gar_reliquaries_namespace}/«STAMP»/syft`, `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/«ANCHOR»`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TAG»` as portion after the final colon
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«PACKAGE_PATH»` is empty: "Package path is empty in locator"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«TAG»` is empty: "Tag is empty in locator"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Jettison*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Will jettison: «INPUT_LOCATOR»`
.. {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Jettison Tag*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#deleting-tags[Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests] with:
... method: `DELETE`
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«PACKAGE_PATH»/manifests/«TAG»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if jettison fails: "Jettison failed with HTTP «STATUS_CODE»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_locator}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Jettisoned or nonexistent: «INPUT_LOCATOR»`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when the tag has been jettisoned from the registry and the jettisoned message is displayed.
The locator-generic shape means a hallmark member, a reliquary tool image, or an enshrinement image are all deleted by the same call — domain identity lives in the locator's package path, not in branched logic.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_hallmark_tally}

NOTE: This operation enumerates every
{rbtga_ark}
in
{rbtgi_repository}
by listing packages under `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/` via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service},
classifying each
{rbtga_hallmark}
by basename presence under its subtree.
A single `packages.list` call returns the full corpus; no per-vessel iteration is required because vessel identity is no longer encoded in the GAR path.

The
{rbtr_retriever}
tallies hallmarks:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_retriever}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_retriever_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Hallmark Packages*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled to `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «RETRIEVER_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name` from the response, strip the resource prefix, and URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`
.. Filter to names whose path under `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/` is exactly two segments (`<hallmark>/<basename>`); excludes both shallower and deeper entries, and excludes anything outside `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/` (reliquaries, enshrines)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PAIRS»` as sorted `<hallmark> <basename>` pairs (one per line). An empty result is a valid outcome — no hallmarks in the repository.

//axhos_step
. *Classify Health Per Hallmark*:
.. Iterate `«PAIRS»` in sort order; each contiguous run of the same hallmark value constitutes one
{rbtga_hallmark}'s
ark inventory.
.. For each hallmark, record whether the basenames
{rbtga_ark_image},
{rbtga_ark_about},
and
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
each appear in its run. Other basenames (`pouch`, `diags`, `attest`) are retained for display but do not affect health classification.
.. Classify:
... `vouched`: `image` + `about` + `vouch` all present
... `pending`: `image` + `about` present, `vouch` absent
... `incomplete`: any other combination (including `image` without `about`, `about` without `image`, or only auxiliary basenames)

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Display Table*:
.. {rbbc_show}
three-column header: `HALLMARK`, `HEALTH`, `BASENAMES`
.. For each hallmark (in sort order):
... {rbbc_show}
hallmark, health state, space-separated list of basenames present under its subtree
.. {rbbc_show}
summary line: `Total hallmarks: N (vouched: V, pending: P, incomplete: I)`

//axhos_step
. *Recommend Next Actions*:
.. If any `pending` hallmarks:
... {rbbc_show}
tabtarget recommendation: {rbtgo_director_vouch} (`rbw-fV`)
.. If any `incomplete` hallmarks:
... {rbbc_show}
tabtarget recommendation: {rbtgo_ark_abjure} (`rbw-fA`) — incomplete typically means the build was interrupted or the about stitch failed

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when the packages listing returns and the classified table displays.
No resources are modified.
Vessel identity is not encoded in the GAR path; restoration of a vessel column, if needed, reads `vessel_name` from `about` or `vouch` metadata and is AAL scope — not performed by tally.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_rekon}

NOTE: This operation reports which canonical members are present under a
hallmark or reliquary subtree in
{rbtgi_repository}
via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.
Raw presence enumeration — no health classification (use {rbtgo_hallmark_tally} for that).

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons over two domains, each backed by a distinct procedure:

* `rbfl_rekon_hallmark` — basenames present under a hallmark subtree
* `rbfl_rekon_reliquary` — tool images present under a reliquary stamp's subtree

Rekon over the {rbtgo_ark_enshrine} domain is intentionally omitted: an enshrinement is a single image per anchor (1-deep), so no presence table is meaningful — {rbtgo_image_audit} covers the catalog and {rbtgo_image_retrieve} covers retrieval.

== Hallmark Rekon

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons basenames under a hallmark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_hallmark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Usage: rbw-irh <hallmark>"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Hallmarks Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled as `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `hallmarks`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK_ROWS»` as `«HALLMARK» «BASENAME»` pairs derived from those entries (a 2-deep enumeration)

//axhos_step
. *Filter to Input Hallmark*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PRESENT»` as the set of basenames in `«HALLMARK_ROWS»` whose hallmark equals `«INPUT_HALLMARK»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«PRESENT»` is empty: "Hallmark not found: «INPUT_HALLMARK»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
table header `BASENAME | EXISTS | PACKAGE-PATH`
.. For each canonical basename in the order
{rbtga_ark_image},
{rbtga_ark_about},
{rbtga_ark_vouch},
`attest`,
{rbtga_ark_pouch},
{rbtga_ark_diags}:
... {rbbc_store}
`«MARK»` as `yes` if `«BASENAME»` ∈ `«PRESENT»`, else `no`
... {rbbc_store}
`«PATH»` as `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/«INPUT_HALLMARK»/«BASENAME»` when `«MARK»` = `yes`, else the literal `(absent)`
... {rbbc_show}
row `«BASENAME» | «MARK» | «PATH»`

== Reliquary Rekon

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons tool images under a reliquary stamp:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_reliquary_stamp}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_STAMP»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Usage: rbw-irr <stamp>"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Reliquaries Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»` from `RBGL_RELIQUARIES_ROOT` (kindled as `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `reliquaries`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARY_ROWS»` as `«STAMP» «TOOL»` pairs derived from those entries (a 2-deep enumeration)

//axhos_step
. *Filter to Input Stamp*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PRESENT»` as the set of tools in `«RELIQUARY_ROWS»` whose stamp equals `«INPUT_STAMP»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«PRESENT»` is empty: "Reliquary stamp not found: «INPUT_STAMP»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_reliquary_stamp}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
table header `TOOL | EXISTS | PACKAGE-PATH`
.. For each canonical reliquary tool in the order `gcloud`, `docker`, `alpine`, `syft`, `binfmt`, `skopeo`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«MARK»` as `yes` if `«TOOL»` ∈ `«PRESENT»`, else `no`
... {rbbc_store}
`«PATH»` as `«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»/«INPUT_STAMP»/«TOOL»` when `«MARK»` = `yes`, else the literal `(absent)`
... {rbbc_show}
row `«TOOL» | «MARK» | «PATH»`

//axhoc_completion
Each procedure completes successfully when the canonical row set has been displayed for the input identifier.
A subtree with no matching row across the canon is treated as the "not present" signal and reported as a fatal — empty subtrees do not yield empty tables.
The operation does not classify health; that is the role of {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}.

