== Reliquary Rekon

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons tool images under a reliquary stamp:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_reliquary_stamp}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_STAMP»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Usage: rbw-irr <stamp>"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Reliquaries Root*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»` from `RBGL_RELIQUARIES_ROOT` (kindled as `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `reliquaries`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name`, strip the resource prefix, URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`, and retain only entries beginning with `«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARY_ROWS»` as `«STAMP» «TOOL»` pairs derived from those entries (a 2-deep enumeration)

//axhos_step
. *Filter to Input Stamp*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PRESENT»` as the set of tools in `«RELIQUARY_ROWS»` whose stamp equals `«INPUT_STAMP»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«PRESENT»` is empty: "Reliquary stamp not found: «INPUT_STAMP»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_reliquary_stamp}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
table header `TOOL | EXISTS | PACKAGE-PATH`
.. For each canonical reliquary tool in the order `gcloud`, `docker`, `alpine`, `syft`, `binfmt`, `skopeo`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«MARK»` as `yes` if `«TOOL»` ∈ `«PRESENT»`, else `no`
... {rbbc_store}
`«PATH»` as `«RELIQUARIES_ROOT»/«INPUT_STAMP»/«TOOL»` when `«MARK»` = `yes`, else the literal `(absent)`
... {rbbc_show}
row `«TOOL» | «MARK» | «PATH»`

//axhoc_completion
Each procedure completes successfully when the canonical row set has been displayed for the input identifier.
A subtree with no matching row across the canon is treated as the "not present" signal and reported as a fatal — empty subtrees do not yield empty tables.
The operation does not classify health; that is the role of {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}.
